title.rendered: World Ranking 2022: Qualifying Phase for the Qatar World Cup: Matches and Results

content.rendered:
The road to the 2022 Qatar World Championship is open in Europe with 55 selections in search of the thirteen places designated to UEFA. The champion of each of the ten groups will have a insured passport.

A very competitive Danish team visits Tel-Aviv. Double presence of LaLiga Santander players in Denmark: Wass (Valencia) and Braithwaite (Barcelona).

BULGARIA – SWITZERLAND

The Swiss come to Sofa led by two players who play in the Premier League: Xhaka at Arsenal and Shaqiri at Liverpool. Xherdan scored a hat-trick in the last Switzerland-Bulgaria match in September 2011.

Chiesa enters the scene. The Juventus attacker played in the house where his father Enrico shone.

A Germany without Kroos. They host Iceland without the madridista and await Musiala’s possible debut.

England broken against San Marino. Southgate will make changes in the first of their three meetings.

‘Lewy’ wants to repeat. The current Golden Boot was already the top scorer heading to the 2018 World Cup. Lewandowski adds 42 goals in 36 duels with Bayern. Great historic scorer from Poland (63 goals) he is the second active European, after CR7, with more goals. The ‘Sousa era’ begins.

the king returns Ibrahimović with Sweden, which will be Spain’s rival on the way to Qatar and in the Euro. Ibra returns 5 years later as a hero and after playing for United, breaking his knee, becoming a reference in the MLS and giving life to Milan.
